# Rinjani design SSOT (Cursor)

For visual work, **do not** use `.stitch/DESIGN.md` or Stitch screenshots as the canonical palette or typography authority.

**Order of truth:**

1. `docs/design-system-overhaul-2026-04-07/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` + `COMPONENT_LIBRARY.md`
2. `packages/shared-ui/src/theme.css` (CSS variables / Tailwind theme)
3. `@rinjani/shared-ui` components

**Code rules:**

- Use semantic classes: `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-muted`, `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, `bg-secondary`, `text-secondary`, etc.
- Avoid raw hex in `className` (e.g. `text-[#101828]`) in feature code; map to theme tokens.
- Reconcile any new color into `theme.css` before widespread use.

See root `AGENTS.md` for the full hierarchy and audit doc pointer.
